# Publish runbook — truewise-data package + dataset DOI

These need your accounts (PyPI, GitHub, Zenodo). The package is built and tested; these
steps release it so others can `pip install` and cite it.

## 1. Publish the dataset as a GitHub Release (do this first — it's the DOI source)

```bash
cd "US datascience projects/truewise"
git tag data-2026-06-10        # tag per Scorecard release
git push origin data-2026-06-10
```
On GitHub: Releases -> Draft a new release -> pick the tag -> attach
`packages/truewise-data/truewise_data/data/value_check.parquet` and
`docs/DATA_DICTIONARY.md` -> Publish.

## 2. Mint a Zenodo DOI (no waiting period)

- Go to zenodo.org -> log in with GitHub -> "GitHub" settings -> flip the toggle ON for
  the `ndranandraj/truewise` repo.
- Zenodo watches for new GitHub Releases; the release from step 1 auto-mints a DOI.
- Add the DOI badge to the repo README and cite it in the package README + methodology.

## 3. Publish the package to PyPI

```bash
pip install build twine
python -m build packages/truewise-data          # builds sdist + wheel into dist/
twine upload packages/truewise-data/dist/*        # paste a PyPI API token when prompted
```
Create the token at pypi.org -> Account settings -> API tokens (scope it to the project
after the first upload). Do NOT paste the token anywhere but twine's prompt.

Then verify a clean install: `pip install truewise-data` in a fresh venv and run the
quickstart from the package README.

## 4. Amplify (highest-leverage, low effort)

- Submit the dataset to **Data Is Plural** (dataisplural.com) — one email, big reach.
- Add a **Hugging Face dataset** page pointing at the same Parquet.
- Log everything (PyPI link, DOI, DIP issue #) in `docs/IMPACT_LOG.md`.

## Notes

- The bundled data is regenerated by `python -m pipeline.build_package_data` and monthly by
  the FVT Monitor workflow, so bump the package version + re-tag on each data refresh.
- Code is MIT; the dataset is CC-BY-4.0.
